<br>
To start it off, I am a lvl 56 mage on Torvonnilous server. I was very excited to see the new FA type items come into the game, and pictured myself with one pretty quick. As we started to piece together the puzzle over the forums here and at CastersRealm, I thought we would be done within a few days... WRONG. Verant has thrown a total curve ball our way, and it really sucks. The long ass camp times and patience that mages must endure to complete this is totally absurd. Some examples...<br>
<br>
My guild has killed Phinigel 9 times the past 2 weeks. It is a large hassle to get 10-12 people ported to Butcher, get them all Waterstones or other breathing equipment, have me swim down to Phin ledge, Call of the Hero all of them so we don't @#%$ up on our way down and die, and kill Phin. There is nothing in it for other people, so they really aren't that motivated. Well Phinigel has decided to keep @#%$ing with me, because he will not drop the god damn staff. We have gotten so many Rods of @#%$ing Malisement, it's sick. We have gotten a Kedge robe (super rare), bard backbone, Enchanter Rods, everything he could possibly drop besides the Elemental Mastery Staff. WTF, it was suppose to be his common drop. I am getting sick and tired of wasting 200pp summoning everybody down there, only to end in futility and alot of pissed off people.<br>
<br>
Next on our list is Innoruuk and his rare as hell Earth Mastery Staff. I realize that I shouldn't expect an Earth staff from every Innoruuk, but maybe how bout just 1? Innoruuk goes down on a weekly basis on Torv, now for about 4 months. His supposedly rare drops (Sode of Empowerment, Rakusha Cloak) have both dropped 3 times, gotten tons of Briarzephyr's and all sorts of @#%$ that decays (SK stuff). But will he ever drop a staff? Hell no. And when he finally does drop it...whaddya know, a level 48 mage picks it up. Spend 5 hours in PoH? Sure you can have a staff. Spend 100+ hours in Hate and 5 Innoruuks? Bend over, you're in our world now.<br>
<br>
Moving on, I decided to try and get the easier items first. So I organize a guild raid on Captain Rottgrime in Overthere. Pleased to say, I actually got the quest piece because he is required to drop it every @#%$ing spawn. Unfortunately, the Dragoon's saw us killing him from half the zone away and decided to run over and say Hi. We all died, but I got a piece, woo@#%$inghoo. Been clearing Undertow in Kedge for awhile. This dude will just not spawn. Cleared him probably 4-5 times, and check on him after every patch, he's a no show. I don't think one Squallsurge Shawl exist on the server, maybe 1 or 2 Blazing Wands that people have thrown away.<br>
<br>
The new rumor is Talendor drops the Burning Embers we need as a *rare* drop. WTF, how can this dude have a rare drop? He has gone down like what, 4 times on all servers since they put him in. I know Afterlife has killed him, maybe FoH if they had any reason to, but Jesus Christ, at least the bards can get their scales from Nagafen or Vox. Our @#%$ only drops from one of the meanest dragons in the game. As a rare drop at that.<br>
<br>
Also tried the Hole and Slizik the Mighty. What a bad idea. We move down to jail on first day. Group is full, so I am just tagging along hoping he spawns. There 3 hours, just lots of ratman warriors. Ok np, just a few more wasted hours. Go back next day, this time in group. Spend 6 hours there, get decent xp. Still no Slizik. Go back third day (today). We are there 3 hours when a ratman guard decides to spawn where Slizik does. This bastard hits for 380 and is almost 100% MR. Made short work of our enchanter trying to slow, so we evacced out. Well when you try and break in, the @#%$ing aggro on these are so huge you get 2-3 at a time. So I will have to organize a 12 man guild raid to go down and clear this bastard, just so I have the right to camp an uber rare spawn for one small part of my quest. And to top it off, nobody even knows if for sure Slizik drops it. This could all be in vain.<br>
<br>
Earlier tonight, guild held a raid on City of Mist to help Shamans with FA quest, get some ORS's, and maybe a Torch of Elements for me. We clear everything, and move to Sky Tower. Kill reaver twice, Neh'Ashiir spawns. His common drop is Torch, rare is ORS. What do you think he @#%$ing drops? ORS of course. Lost the random on that. So we sit there for 2 @#%$ing hours waiting for reaver to respawn. All that junk up there is green trash except the reavers, so lots of more wasted time. The reaver never does respawn, so we leave. Yet another long ass boring camp with ridiculous respawn. I read a post on Neh'Ashiir where a guild on Veeshan got the Torch of Elements in 4 straight spawns, yet not tonight while I was there. <br>
<br>
I don't really know what to say anymore. I mean I have busted my balls tryign to collect pieces for this quest, only to end in futility. For @#%$'s sake, I see these pictures of 6 rogues standing back to back to back all with their Uber items they got on the same night. What the hell is wrong with this picture. The mage epic probably won't be completed for another 2 months just because of the obscurity of these items, but 6 rogues can all do there 1 week after the quest comes on. Makes me think Verant hired two different types of people to do these quest. Potheads and PhD's. Guess which one we got.<br>
<br>
